Turkish security forces killed three
members of the Kurdistan Workersâ€™ Party, or PKK, during a clash
in the eastern province of Tunceli, according to state-run
Anatolia  news agency .  Fighting broke out late yesterday as Turkish forces were
conducting surveillance, the news agency said today, citing a
statement from the governorship.  The PKK, which is listed as a terrorist organization by
 Turkey , the U.S. and the European Union, has been fighting for
autonomy in the southeast since 1984 in a conflict that has
